RIYADH: Saudi Arabia's Deputy Foreign Minister Waleed Al-Khuraiji received Assistant Minister and Director General of the Middle Eastern and African Affairs Bureau at the Japanese Ministry of Foreign Affairs Kansuke Nagaoka in Riyadh on Sunday. During the meeting, they reviewed bilateral relations between Japan and the Kingdom, and ways to enhance them in all fields, as well as issues of common interest. The reception was attended by the Ambassador of Japan to the Kingdom Iwai Fumio. Also on Sunday, Al-Khuraiji received Ambassador of Germany to the Kingdom Dieter Lamle. They reviewed relations between Germany and the Kingdom, and ways to enhance them.